Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 05-Mar-2025

1. Introduction
ClickCounter ("we," "our," or "us") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect any personal information you provide while using our ClickCounter App (the "App"). By using the App, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.

2. Information We Collect
We do not collect or store any personal data from users.
The only data we might get are the crash reports provided by Google to identify and fix bugs

3. How We Use Information
The limited data we collect is used solely to improve the App’s functionality and user experience. We do not sell, rent, or share your information with third parties.

4. Third-Party Services
The App may use third-party services, such as Google Analytics or Firebase, to enhance functionality. These services may collect data as per their privacy policies. Please refer to their respective privacy policies for more details.

5. Data Security
Refer to the default security measures provided by Google. However, no method of transmission over the internet is completely secure.

6. Children’s Privacy
Our App is not intended for children under 18. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.

7. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted within the App or on our website.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact me at maitreya.save@gmail.com